<subSubSection id="C343BD964B6BFFE95C970F8DADC9FC74" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE6EE1D4B6BFFE95C970F8DABA4FCC1" blockId="76.[151,1436,325,970]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B92D320F4B6BFFE95C970F8DA856FCB1" bold="true" box="[197,318,757,783]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC893EC4B6BFFE95D1E0F8DAB73FCB1" author="Kolomiets, N. G." box="[332,539,757,783]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="53 - 76" refId="ref59159" refString="Kolomiets, N. G. (1970) Parasitic Diptera of the genus Dexia Mg. (Diptera, Tachinidae) to the USSR fauna. Novye i maloizvestnye vidy fauny Sibiri, 3, 53 - 76. [In Russian with English summary.]" type="journal article" year="1970">Kolomiets (1970)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from 
<collectingCountry id="F34EAE8D4B6BFFE95F3B0F8DAAB3FCB1" box="[873,987,757,783]" name="Mongolia" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
and later 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC893EC4B6BFFE9581D0F8DAD9DFCB1" author="Mesnil, L. P." box="[1103,1269,757,783]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref59533" refString="Mesnil, L. P. (1980) 64 f. Dexiinae. Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region, 9 (Lieferung 323), 1 - 52." type="book chapter" year="1980">Mesnil (1980)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed it in detail. As we were unable to see this species, the characters mentioned above were taken from 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC893EC4B6BFFE959730E62A98EFCE4" author="Kolomiets, N. G." pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="53 - 76" refId="ref59159" refString="Kolomiets, N. G. (1970) Parasitic Diptera of the genus Dexia Mg. (Diptera, Tachinidae) to the USSR fauna. Novye i maloizvestnye vidy fauny Sibiri, 3, 53 - 76. [In Russian with English summary.]" type="journal article" year="1970">Kolomiets (1970)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC893EC4B6BFFE95D730E38A8A7FCE4" author="Mesnil, L. P." box="[289,463,832,858]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref59533" refString="Mesnil, L. P. (1980) 64 f. Dexiinae. Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region, 9 (Lieferung 323), 1 - 52." type="book chapter" year="1980">Mesnil (1980)</bibRefCitation>
. The date of collection of the 
<typeStatus id="54E250BF4B6BFFE95F6A0E38AAC8FCE4" box="[824,928,832,858]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">holotype</typeStatus>
is different in the Russian description and English summary; we cited the former one here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE6EE1D4B6BFFE95C970EF2ADC9FC74" blockId="76.[151,1436,325,970]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
This species appears to resemble 
<taxonomicName id="4C59959E4B6BFFE95E0D0EF2AB8BFC1D" box="[607,739,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Dexia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis id="B92D320F4B6BFFE95E0D0EF2AB1CFC1D" box="[607,628,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92D320F4B6BFFE95ED70EF2AB8BFC1D" box="[645,739,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">flavipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but may be distinguished from it in having very narrow prosternum, and 1st flagellomere as long as palpus and 2.0−2.5 times as long as pedicel.
</paragraph>
